{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/uproot5/pulls/88", "id": 476491505, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NDc2NDkxNTA1", "html_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/uproot5/pull/88", "diff_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/uproot5/pull/88.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep/uproot5/pull/88.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/uproot5/issues/88", "number": 88, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "Fixes #36 by replacing range with xrange in Python 2.", "user": {"login": "jpivarski", "id": 1852447, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE4NTI0NDc=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1852447?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski", "html_url": "https://github.com/jpivarski", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jpivarski/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "Uproot's deserialization is based on nominal versions of classes first, then falls back to streamers if they're wrong. Streamers being wrong can have you thinking you need to iterate over 1329201155 elements in a TObjArray before the error gets fixed. In Python 2, `range(1329201155)` constructs a list, which uses an enormous amount of memory. `uproot4._util.range` is `range` in Python 3 and `xrange` in Python 2; we just need to use `uproot4._util.range` wherever we'd use `range`.\r\n\r\nIssue #36 warned that it might be a deep bug, affecting Python 3 in unknown and apparently invisible ways. It's not.", "created_at": "2020-08-31T19:21:10Z", "updated_at": "2020-08-31T19:37:38Z", "closed_at": "2020-08-31T19:37:34Z", "merged_at": "2020-08-31T19:37:34Z", "merge_commit_sha": "9ff06a4e5e80bcd6501eb9647a907b8a0d8fb771", "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels": [], "milestone": null, "draft": false, "commits_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/uproot5/pulls/88/commits", "review_comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/uproot5/pulls/88/comments", "review_comment_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/uproot5/pulls/comments{/number}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/uproot5/issues/88/comments", "statuses_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-hep/uproot5/statuses/7a6d03d51b56092995c63c040895073d1d2a3949", "head": {"label": "scikit-hep:jpivarski/fix-python2-memory-issue", "ref": "jpivarski/fix-python2-memory-issue", "sha": "7a6d03d51b56092995c63c040895073d1d2a3949", "user": {"login": "scikit-hep", "id": 23454624, "node_id": "MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjIzNDU0NjI0", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/23454624?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep", "html_url": "https://github.com/scikit-hep", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/scikit-hep/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.g